(ooc: sorry i'm so late on getting back, guys! my son got sick, and i didnt 
have time to rp)

Mantle looked up at Prowl and smiled. Even though Prowl had changed since 
Mantle last saw him, Mantle could still recognize him through telepathy. He 
stretched out a hand for a handshake.

"Hello Prowl." He said. "Its been a while since we lost communication with 
you and Striker."

Mantle knew that Cinder was standing behind him, and he could feel in his 
mind that her spark was beating like mad. But he could understand. After 
months of worrying, Cinder finally found the bot she'd been worrying about. 
To her, the fact that the rest of the team was gone wasn't as bad as it 
would have been if Prowl had died too. Aqua was holding Cinder by the 
shoulders, something that Mantle was thankful for since it prevented her 
from running up to Prowl.
